      "side": 1,
      "message": "if I may chime in. Namespace or no namespace appended doesn\u0027t really matter as the whole ONAP meant to be deployed in a single namespace. It boils down to how service resolution works in K8S.\nBasically, within the same namespace, all services are accessible by their name.\nWithin different namespace, services are accessible through the combinaison of their name dot the namespace.\n\nExample:\n\nnamespace1:\n  pap\n  pdp\n\nnamespace2:\n  aai\n\nFor pap to reach pdp, the following can be used:\n  pdp\n  pdp.namespace1\n\nFor pap to reach aai, the following should be used:\n  aai.namespace2\n\nIf the second example, if you don\u0027t append the namespace, K8S will lookup the aai service within namespace1, and that would fail.\n\nBasically, it is good practice to append the release name, as that\u0027s what is being use to define the namespace. That will allow one to deploy component as they intend, if they don\u0027t want to follow the recommandation of deploying in a single namespace.\n\nHope it helps understanding.",
      "parentUuid": "bada0100_e61406f7",
